In a press release, the [agriculture] minister's office reports on the current analyses: "To date [2 Oct 2018], 74 boars have been analysed, 48 of which have been found in the perimeter, of which there are now 28 viropositive cases. The 26 boars found outside the perimeter, as well as wild boar poached last [Sat 29 Sep 2018], were all negative."

