African swine fever - News in Belgium (updated 2 Oct 2018)
----------------------------------------------------------
Since [13 Sep 2018], 28 cases of African swine fever [ASF] have been detected in wild boars found dead in the Etalle region, in the province of Luxembourg.

Coordinated actions between different agencies are being taken to prevent the spread of the virus at the level of wildlife and hog farms. The competences are indeed divided between the regions for all the wildlife and the FASFC for all that concerns domestic pigs.

Under a mutual agreement between the AFSCA and the Walloon Region, an infected zone has been defined around the detected cases.[See URL above for map]. In this area, measures are taken for both wild boar and domestic pigs. The measures concerning wild boar and the use of forests are taken care by the Walloon Region and can be consulted at http://www.wallonie.be/fr/actualites/mesures-de-lutte-contre-la-peste-porcine-africaine (in French).

With regard to domestic pigs, all the enforcement measures are available at http://www.afsca.be/ppa/mesures/ (in French).

